"Contingency planning in bank data processing is necessary to minimize the damage caused by unexpected and undesirable events affecting information processing. The destruction of delay of this flow of information results in millions of dollars of losses each year. Such losses are caused by catastrophes that cannot be prevented readily and whose probability of occurence is low and by events that can be expected with reasonable frequency, such as hardware or power failure. The purpose of contingency planning is to minimize the operational and financial impact of unfavourable events regardless of their magnitute. Our dependence on the computer system has increased to the point where reversion to a manual system, if at all possible, would have an unacceptable cost in time and money terms."
